description: The rambunctious presidential debate Thursday night left some Republican candidates shining and others stung. Here are some highlights and low lights from the prime-time showdown.
title: How the Republican Candidates Fared in the First Debate
title_page: How the Republican Candidates Fared in the First Debate - The New York Times
maintext:
Rivals Jab at Donald Trump as Republican Debate Becomes Testy
Mr. Trump was put on the defensive from the start of the debate, not only by his rivals but by the debate moderators from Fox News.
